INSERT INTO `notes`
VALUES (665, NULL, 233, 608,
        '<p>Governance tokens gives holders the right to control&nbsp;the direction of decentralized financial projects. These tokens are becoming more popular in the cryptocurrency economy as they give users a direct participation in managing DeFi platforms. It can be defined as the fuel that drives the blockchain-based voting process. They are used to support or oppose any changes. Token holders can also vote on new changes to the protocol. A typical governance token system is that each token has one vote. This means that if the token holder has more tokens, he will have more control of&nbsp;the protocol.</p>\n',
        '2020-09-28 10:59:49', '2020-09-28 11:00:47', 0, 1, 0, 1, 233);
INSERT INTO `notes`
VALUES (666, NULL, 230, 616,
        '<p>There is no doubt that using a platform like BlockFi is more risky than storing cryptocurrencies in your wallet. These platforms are typically investment vehicles that offer lucrative interest on your cryptocurrencies. BlockFi is a platform for lending and borrowing cryptocurrencies, which was launched in August 2017. The company is one of the pioneers of cryptocurrencies supported by large investment funds, among others: Morgan Creek, Winklevoss Capital, Galaxy Digital, Coinbase Ventures.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>BlockFi currently offers three products on its platform, which is earning interest on cryptocurrencies, loans against your cryptocurrencies and trading. For example, you might be earning 6-8% interest on bitcoins, but you want your payout to be in one of the supported coins like ETH or PAX. BlockFi mainly makes money by lending crypto assets to other institutional counterparties to trade and borrow cryptocurrency. Some of these borrowers are traders and mutual funds, market makers (OTC), companies that require cryptocurrency stocks to provide liquidity to clients.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n',
        '2020-09-28 12:59:59', '2020-09-28 12:59:59', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `notes`
VALUES (667, NULL, 230, 601,
        '<p>Burning coins in cryptocurrencies means sending some coins of your native cryptocurrency or other currency to a public address from which you can never spend those specific coins because the private keys of such an address are unreachable. This public address should be available on the blockchain so that anyone can view it. transactions. The whole process is done by sending some of the coins to the &quot;eater address&quot;, which is often referred to as &quot;black hole&quot;, private keys to this address are not available to anyone. Except&nbsp;the return lines to the &#39;eater&#39; address are not recoverable and cannot be reused. These coins are thus withdrawn from circulation and are publicly registered and verified on the blockchain. There are few&nbsp;reasons why burning coins is a good idea. For example, a larger and more effective consensus mechanism. This applies to coins that adopt Proof-of-Burn (POB) as a consensus mechanism. POB is a unique way to buy consensus in a distributed network, requiring participants, miners and users to burn some coins. Reducing supply should (but not always), but increasing demand is the so-called deflation system.</p>\r\n',
        '2020-09-28 13:30:15', '2020-09-28 13:30:15', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `notes`
VALUES (668, NULL, 230, 594,
        '<p>Finding errors on any site and fixing the error from that site is called error reward. Large companies such as Google, Facebook, Microsoft have their own bounty platform where companies create their accounts to participate in this program. The easiest way is to go to the bug bounty platform and find the bug on different companies&#39; websites and report it to them. This company will work with you to resolve the error.<br />\nIf you found an error on Google, Google pays a lot of money, it depends on the type of error you found on this page. If you&#39;ve found a bug that could leak Google users&#39; data, then Google will pay you a lot more money. If you found a bug that is irrelevant to Google, Google may or may not give you money as there is no threat to Google from the error. Various projects and platforms in the crypto world are putting out their own bug bounty programs that anyone can participate. You have to be up-to-date with the crypto world.</p>\n',
        '2020-09-28 13:58:43', '2020-09-28 13:59:03', 0, 0, 0, 1, 230);
INSERT INTO `notes`
VALUES (669, NULL, 238, 586, '<p>Could someone explain to me what is this staking?&nbsp;</p>\r\n',
        '2020-09-28 16:02:34', '2020-09-28 16:02:34', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `notes`
VALUES (670, 669, 236, 586,
        'You may think of staking as a less resource-intensive alternative to mining. It consists of storing resources in a crypto wallet to ensure the safety and operation of blockchain networks. Simply put, staking is about blocking cryptocurrencies to receive rewards.\n\nIn most cases, you will be able to stake your coins directly from your wallet, such as Trust Wallet. On the other hand, many crypto exchanges offer their users a staking services. Binance Staking allows you to win prizes in a very simple way - just keep your coins in the stock market. \n\nTo better understand what staking is, you must first understand how Proof of Stake (PoS) works. PoS is a consensus mechanism that allows blockchainers to operate more energy-efficient, while maintaining a decent degree of decentralization (at least in theory).',
        '2020-09-28 16:05:03', '2020-09-28 16:05:03', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `notes`
VALUES (671, NULL, 238, 593,
        '<p>Airdrop is basically a drop, i.e., distribution of free crypto in the community. The purpose of this is to arouse interest around a given project and increase its demand, which translates into higher prices.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>There are two types of free token distribution. As a reward for having specific cryptocurrencies in wallet and giveaway - a free airdrop for doing a few simple steps.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>At the first opportunity we are rewarded by project developers for keeping cryptocurrency on their official wallets. Personally, I&#39;ve already received aidrop many times at the ETH, NEO or Waves wallets. Depending on the funds we have, we get directly proportional amounts of &quot;dropped&quot; tokens. The bigger the capital, the bigger the rewards.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The second option is available for everyone. It consists mainly in filling in a form, in which you usually have to use social media to: &quot;Like&quot;, sharing, subscribing to/observing the indicated accounts or profiles. Finally, we provide our public key, i.e. the wallet address, so that after the action is over the funds will land there.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Most airdrops are carried out on the Ethereum platform, so the ERC20 token wallet, called MetaMask, will definitely be useful.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I also recommend token wallets on the NEO platform - as well as the Waves desktop wallet, which can be downloaded here https://wavesplatform.com/.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The basic requirement is also to have accounts in services such as Facebook. Twitter, Telegram, Medium, Reddit, Instagram.</p>\r\n',
        '2020-09-28 16:10:15', '2020-09-28 16:10:15', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `notes`
VALUES (672, 621, 238, 592,
        'Every crypto exchange a bush company. There is ALWAYS a risk that it will fall. Many people has literally lost hundreds of thousands due to the collapse of the exchange. MtGox, Minpal, Cryptsy, Btc-e and or bitcurex and also smaller exchanges was affected. Therefore, because of this experience, it is recommended to always be careful when it comes to cash deposit on a given exchange.\n',
        '2020-09-28 16:13:05', '2020-09-28 16:13:05', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `notes`
VALUES (673, NULL, 238, 601,
        '<p>This is nothing more than getting rid of a certain amount of cryptocurrencies completely from circulation.<br />\r\nMost often such actions are carried out by the creators themselves. These are not accidental decisions, one can even say that they are frequent practices, and the creators gain certain benefits from such actions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>When the tokens are burned, we can cause deflation, which at the same time will significantly increase the overall value for the actual cryptocurrency.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Larger players on the &nbsp;market do not have to go for this type of treatment, but smaller platforms, must control the flow of virtual currency in such a way as to always earn on it.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This is not in any way a practical currency denomination, so it cannot be compared in any way, at least not as literally as we would like it to. Those dealing with cryptocurrencies are not always really aware of how this process actually works in practical life.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The token burning procedure itself makes the currency that is being burned cannot be used in the future anymore.</p>\r\n',
        '2020-09-28 16:15:48', '2020-09-28 16:15:48', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `notes`
VALUES (674, NULL, 238, 600,
        '<p>Phishing is a scam used by online criminals to obtain valuable information, such as logins and passwords oraz credit card numbers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The name evokes sound associations with fishing. Criminals, like anglers, use a properly prepared &quot;lure&quot;. In this role they usually use fake e-mails and text messages. More and more often scammers act also through communicators and community portals.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In order to inspire the trust of the victim, phishers impersonate commonly recognized companies and institutions - banks, offices, auction portals, courier and telecommunication companies. With the help of fake messages they try to persuade the victim to click on the link in the message. It usually leads to a website created by fraudsters. It is deceptively similar to the authentic website of the company or institution from which the message allegedly comes - but in fact, it is a trap set for careless internet users.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The fraudsters use the fake website to obtain the data that the victim himself makes available to them, they are convinced that they are logging into the authentic transactional service of their bank. It is also common practice to send out fake e-mails, the content of which encourages Internet users to download a harmful file, which is included in the attachment.</p>\r\n',
        '2020-09-28 16:17:58', '2020-09-28 16:17:58', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `notes`
VALUES (675, NULL, 238, 599,
        '<p>How does gold is compared to cryptocurrency? The crux of the matter is that it is a physical resource and Bitcoin a digital resource. So each asset has its strengths and weaknesses. BTC is easier to transport (actually, this problem does not exist here at all) or hide.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Today, both gold and BTC function similarly. Their rates are in a way indicators of whether the world is doing well or badly. The cryptocurrency was already gaining during the Cyprus crisis, which caused fears of a complete collapse of the banking system. The course also responded positively to the results of the referendum on brexit. In fact, the digital currency itself was created as a form of rebellion against the political and financial mainstream from the last crisis of a decade ago.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Today, when further US policy towards China, tariffs and Federal Reserve operations are uncertain, it is a good idea to buy not only gold but also Bitcoins (and/or leading altcoins or tokens).</p>\r\n',
        '2020-09-28 16:20:17', '2020-09-28 16:20:17', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
