INSERT INTO `notes`
VALUES (819, NULL, 194, 702,
        '<p>Pojawia si nowa oferta pracy wydana przez Ripple na stronie Greenhouse.io. Z ogoszenia wynika, e Ripple chce zatrudni starszego dyrektora ds.zaangaowania banku centralnego. Ripple poszukuje sprawdzonego lidera, kt&oacute;ry bdzie kierowa strategi, partnerstwami i projektami z bankami centralnymi na caym wiecie.</p>\n\n<p>Wedug dyrektora generalnego B.Garlinghouse Xrp moe suy jako most wymiany cyfrowych walut fiat. Ripple ujawnio, e zamierza zawrze partnerstwo z projektami CBDC i zarzdza list docelow bank&oacute;w i projekt&oacute;w oraz sterowa procesem transakcji od pocztku do koca. XRPL zosta celowo zbudowany do przeprowadzania transakcji zar&oacute;wno natywnych, neutralnych aktywach jak i na aktywach nowo wyemitowanych.&nbsp;Xrp nie jest w stanie obsuy wszystkich patnoci na wiecie, ale moe by pewnego rodzaju orodkiem lub krgosupem, kt&oacute;ry zapewni szybkie midzynarodowe rozliczenia.</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://boards.greenhouse.io/ripple/jobs/2455864\" style=\"text-decoration:none\">https://boards.greenhouse.io/ripple/jobs/2455864</a></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n',
        '2020-11-23 15:28:35', '2020-11-23 15:30:21', 0, 0, 0, 1, 194);
INSERT INTO `notes`
VALUES (820, NULL, 233, 701,
        '<p>According to CEO B. Garlinghouse, Xrp can serve as a fiat digital currency exchange bridge. Ripple has announced that is intend to partner with CBDC projects of&nbsp; the banks and manage the projects, target list and steer the transaction process from start to finish.</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://ripple.com/insights/ripple-hosts-worlds-central-banks-to-explore-next-generation-of-payments/\" style=\"text-decoration:none\">https://ripple.com/insights/ripple-hosts-worlds-central-banks-to-explore-next-generation-of-payments/</a></p>\n\n<p>https://www.crypto-news-flash.com/ripple-confirms-bank-of-america-boa-as-a-client/</p>\n\n<p>XRP and XRPL was purposely built to transact both native neutral assets and newly issued assets. Recently Ripple published job offers &lt;<a href=\"https://boards.greenhouse.io/ripple/jobs/2455864\" style=\"text-decoration:none\">LINK</a>&gt; on the <a href=\"https://boards.greenhouse.io/ripple/jobs/2455864\" style=\"text-decoration:none\">Greenhouse.io</a> website. Ripple is looking to hire a senior director of central bank involvement, according to the announcement. Ripple is looking for a proven leader to lead strategy, partnerships and projects with central banks around the world. Xrp cannot handle all payments in the world, but it can be some kind of hub or backbone to ensure fast international settlements.</p>\n',
        '2020-11-23 15:52:29', '2020-11-25 12:34:14', 0, 0, 0, 1, 233);
INSERT INTO `notes`
VALUES (821, NULL, 239, 693,
        '<p>The fee results from the given traffic in the network. If you want to have a transaction as soon as possible, you will pay more, the bigger the network traffic is (there are too many transactions to handle, so you have to pay more).</p>\n\n<p>Note that you have been charged three times 100sat/B and a second time as much. If these are transactions coming out of BitBay, they charge a lump sum - as you can see above. The exchanges usually take 0.0005 BTC or 0.001 BTC from the payout and release transactions for 100sat/b or more. In general, the exchanges give quite high fees for the transfer to pass quickly, but they charge a lump sum from the client.</p>\n\n<p>Transactions are at significant intervals, so the BTC price was also different. Therefore, the fee in USD is different.</p>\n\n<p>To sum up: this is basically the norm</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n',
        '2020-11-23 18:51:19', '2020-11-23 18:51:24', 0, 0, 0, 1, 239);
INSERT INTO `notes`
VALUES (822, NULL, 235, 676,
        '<p>Arbitrage is purchase of a good or an asset on a market where its price is relatively lower in order to simultaneously resell that good or asset on another market where its price is relatively higher. Such a transaction is carried out without risk. The essence of arbitrage is to notice the difference in prices of the same product on different markets or on the same market. If this difference is greater than the transaction costs, the investor, buying the product on the cheaper market and selling on the more expensive market, makes a profit.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Arbitrage leads to limitation of the price difference of the same good or asset on different markets to the margin depending on the size of transaction costs, thus increasing the efficiency of markets.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In banking it is a buyout of securities on the markets, where quotations of given assets are beneficial, in order to resell them with profit on other markets. In financial mathematics, arbitrage is the strategy of buying or selling securities, currencies, commodities or financial derivatives with a positive probability of profit without the risk of loss.</p>\r\n',
        '2020-11-23 19:08:36', '2020-11-23 19:08:36', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `notes`
VALUES (823, NULL, 235, 680,
        '<p>Paxos began trading its PAX Gold (PAXG) token, according to information available on the CoinMarketCap news page on September 27, 2019. Each issued token is to be covered with one ounce of gold. The gold will be physically stored in a bank in London.PAX Gold therefore has a fixed market value, but is consistent with the value of gold. It can be assumed that the price of the token will vary according to the price of gold. The token will react to price fluctuations, positively or negatively. At the time of writing this text, its price is about USD 1700, which is actually equal to the price of one ounce of gold.PAX Gold is one of the so-called ERC-20 tokens. This means that the PAXG operates in the Ethereum network, using its blockchain under strict (defined) conditions of this token, which the publisher initially specifies.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>They are currently traded on the Bithumb and HitBTC exchanges. 99.99% of the transactions take place on the first of these exchanges, as opposed to the dollar.&nbsp;</p>\r\n',
        '2020-11-23 19:10:44', '2020-11-23 19:10:44', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
