INSERT INTO `notes`
VALUES (909, NULL, 238, 692,
        '<p>There is no such thing as a minimum age after which you can buy Bitcoin. You just need to be mature enough to realize what you are doing.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In practice, however, most cryptocurrency operations require a minimum age of 18. So, to be able to exchange, for example, you must be of legal age, which meets the KYC requirements. It does not matter how clearly you filled out your documents when logging in: if you are underage, you will not be able to buy bitcoin. How can minors buy bitcoins without breaking the law?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Teenagers who want to buy bitcoin have many options available. &quot;Legality&quot; of each method is questionable, but technically they work:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>eBay: This platform isn&#39;t just for athletic shoes and electronics. Sellers can also encourage you to buy Bitcoin. Using eBay and Paypal to buy small amounts of bitcoin isn&#39;t difficult, but before you buy it, you should check the seller&#39;s ratings to make sure they&#39;re not a scammer<br />\r\nBitcoin ATMs: ATMs are theoretically the ideal way to buy cryptocurrency. In practice there are not many of them, so unless you live i big city, it won&#39;t be easy.&nbsp;<br />\r\nLocalbitcoins: technically, the same rules that apply to cryptocurrency exchanges also apply to sites like Localbitcoins.com. Basic verification is very easy and once completed, you can buy and sell for free P2P (person to person) and transfer money directly from your bank account. You can also meet the sellers in person and buy bitcoin for cash, but it is recommended to be careful, especially for the first purchase. It is better to go with an adult for your first purchase.<br />\r\nP2P moneychangers: In addition to Localbitcoins.com, there are sites like Solidi in the UK, which advises users that &quot;those under the age of 18 who wish to trade should contact them first.&quot; Those under the age of 16 can also trade and will only receive low purchase limits. Bitcoinprijzen in the Netherlands is another place where people under the age of 18 appear to be buying cryptocurrencies using iDEAL.<br />\r\nLocal crypto community: check out fanebook fanpageg, here you will find cryptocurrency enthusiasts who can sell you something. Just write. Users looking to support Bitcoin in the community will be happy to help you. As always, be careful when you meet someone you don&#39;t know. And don&#39;t pay until you see that the transaction has gone through.<br />\r\nSome young people being creative have bought gift cards from Amazon and exchanged them on sites like Paxful for Bitcoins.&nbsp;</p>\r\n',
        '2021-02-04 22:36:24', '2021-02-04 22:36:24', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `notes`
VALUES (910, NULL, 238, 726,
        '<p>Well, in this case, there are several options:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Wait until processing a transaction with such a fee against the others at Mempool is attractive to miners. However, it might as well be cancelled after a few days and return to the original address.<br />\r\nThe ViaBTC mine has provided a tool on its website to speed up the joining of transactions to the block. If the fee was extremely low then this system will also reject the processing as not worthwhile.<br />\r\nIf you were using an updated Electrum wallet then it is possible that you had the Replace-by-fee option set in your preferences and you can then, say, &quot;update&quot; your transfer so that it has the appropriate transaction fee.<br />\r\nIf you feel up to it, some people advise copying your wallet to manually remove the transaction that is stuck in order to try sending it again. However, this is a process that requires knowledge of how the wallet is structured.<br />\r\nThe &quot;Child Pays For Parent&quot; method (CPFP) is a way in which the recipient increases the fee of the transfer going to them. This is a significant difference from RBF because there the sender updated the transfer.</p>\r\n',
        '2021-02-04 22:39:17', '2021-02-04 22:39:17', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `notes`
VALUES (911, NULL, 234, 726,
        '<p>As a last resort, you can use a method to push our unconfirmed transaction called Child Pays for Parent. This method involves making another transaction that has a higher transaction fee set, so that the miners spread it between the two transactions and thus also approve the earlier one that got stuck. How it works. The method is to execute another trade using the UTXO (output) from the one that is unconfirmed. This means that in order for the miners to confirm the child transaction, they must first attach the parent transaction to the block that previously had too low a fee. Chil Pays for Parent is also available in most notable wallets as a default solution.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Basically, all leading wallets nowadays suggest the optimal transaction commissions themselves based on the current situation in the network, so it is worth taking advantage of these facilities.</p>\r\n',
        '2021-02-04 22:41:38', '2021-02-04 22:41:38', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
