VALUES (1452, 236, '2020-09-19 15:40:42', '2020-09-19 15:40:42', 1,
        '{\"message\":{\"content\":593,\"type_id\":2,\"title\":\"What is Airdrop?\",\"reason\":1,\"comment_id\":615,\"description\":\"<p>Airdrop is a form of gift from developers of a given cryptocurrency and an effective marketing tool. The airdrops take place at the moment of announcement to the network of the block with a predefined number. If Airdrop is scheduled for block number 50, at the time of announcement of the block in the network, we receive a new currency. &nbsp;In the case of airdrops you get new cryptocurrencies in a certain ratio, often higher than 1:1 e.g. 1:10.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To receive the Airdrops, often the only requirement is to store coins from the appropriate block in your wallet. Examples of such drops are Byteball, Stellar lumen and OmiseGo.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>It happens that airdrops are a surprise. &nbsp;It is worth checking your wallets, because it may turn out that you received a nice gift. Platforms such as Waves or Komodo surprised their owners by making airdrops without any notice.<\\/p>\\r\\n\"}}',
        615, 235, 5, 6, 0, 'en_US');
