VALUES (2130, 246, '2021-01-15 16:15:44', '2021-01-15 16:15:44', 1,
        '{\"message\":{\"content\":751,\"type_id\":2,\"title\":\"What is the difference between hard fork and soft fork ??\",\"reason\":1,\"comment_id\":857,\"description\":\"<p>Hard and soft forks are needed for the long-term success of a blockchain network. They allow many updates in a decentralized system even if there is no central authority. While both forks form a split, in a soft fork only that blockchain remains valid. However, a hard fork causes two blockchains to exist side by side, and the former is abandoned by users.<\\/p>\\r\\n\"}}',
